CH11: Storage
- HDD (Hard Disk Drive)
  arm movement,
  sector, track, cylinder
  block
- NVM (Non-Volatile Memory)
  vs DRAM
  + SSD (Solid State Drive)
- disk attachment: BUS
  + SCSI (small computer system interface)
  + IDE (Integrated Device Electronics): pc
  + SAS (Serial Attached SCSI)
  + SATA (Serial ATA: Advanced Technology Attachment)
  +NVMe (NVM express)
   ~ used with SSD
along with NVMe, PCIe ( P refers to peripheral)
  PCIe + NVMe

* formatting: 
  - low-level (physical) formatting
